    <persName type="additional" subtype="title">2d Baron Lurgan</persName>
    
    <note type="dates"><date>1831–82</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Lord lieutenant of county Armagh, Ireland, 1864–82. Lord-in-waiting to Queen Victoria, 1869–74. Kept racehorses, but was best known as a breeder and owner of greyhounds, the most famous of which was Master Mcgrath.</p></note>
